description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;I help to make a difference!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;Prisons are one of the most challenging, yet rewarding places for healthcare professionals to work - if you’re looking for a role where you can develop your existing skills and learn something new every day, then this is the place to be.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Practice Plus Group are the Health in Justice Market leader, providing healthcare services to offenders across the country. Our model of care is our Wellbeing Approach – an integrated, comprehensive approach in recognition of the fact prisoners are a socially-excluded group with healthcare needs which are complex and often associated with poor outcomes. It adopts the premise no single health/wellbeing factor can be taken in isolation of other motivational issues which might impact a person’s care.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We are looking for a Regional Administrator to work with our Thames Valley prison cluster and support the regional management in day to day administration tasks.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; In return for your hard work you will..&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Receive an annual salary of up to £21,000 per annum depending on experience. You&#39;ll also get a number of benefits including a company contributory pension scheme, 25 days annual leave plus 8 public bank holidays.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Other benefits include cycle to work scheme plus training and clerical development opportunities.&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Onsite benefits at our prisons include access to an onsite gym, free parking and subsidised café/restaurant.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;What do we need from you so you can do the job?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span&gt;Your role will be to support the Regional and Deputy Regional Managers providing a day-to-day administrative and personal support service. As you will be working inside the prisons often, you will need to be confident to work in this setting. This is a regional post across the Thames Valley region and the expected base would be the nearest prison to your home address. We are also flexible  in working locations so we can implement a structure for you to have a mix of home working as well as site working. You will be expected to travel across the region to attend meetings and take minutes as and when required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Next steps&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are shortlisted, you will be contacted by the Internal Recruiter for this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span&gt; The recruiter will submit your CV to the hiring manager and in turn we will arrange an interview for you to attend if the hiring manager feels that you are suitable for the job.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For further information, please contact us on the details provided.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;More information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a full vacancy working 37.5 hours per week. The salary for this role is up to £21,000 - dependent on experience.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that we reserve the right to close this advert earlier than stated if a sufficient number of applications have been received.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Offers of employment are subject to Practice Plus Group Terms &amp; Conditions and receipt of satisfactory references, an enhanced DBS check and prison vetting.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; At &lt;span&gt;Practice Plus Group &lt;/span&gt;we actively promote diversity and equal opportunities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
